00:01:11,640 --> 00:01:13,940
Form a friendly expression on your face

24
00:01:14,460 --> 00:01:17,420
as if you are showing friendship for someone you care about

25
00:01:19,280 --> 00:01:21,560
Although this may feel unnatural to do

26
00:01:22,100 --> 00:01:24,980
expressions can affect systems in your brain

27
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:28,540
and change the way you think or the way you feel

28
00:01:31,760 --> 00:01:33,940
So now with our compassion posture

29
00:01:35,340 --> 00:01:36,820
we are going to move gently

30
00:01:36,980 --> 00:01:40,180
into soothing and grounding breathing rhythms

31
00:01:41,680 --> 00:01:44,340
We breathe in gently through the nose

32
00:01:44,800 --> 00:01:46,620
for around five seconds

33
00:01:47,660 --> 00:01:50,140
noticing the stillness at the top of the breath

34
00:01:52,540 --> 00:01:53,860
and then breathing out

35
00:01:54,240 --> 00:01:55,700
for around five seconds

36
00:01:56,020 --> 00:01:58,840
noticing the stillness at the bottom of the breath

37
00:02:02,800 --> 00:02:04,060
We are breathing in

38
00:02:04,460 --> 00:02:05,360
and out

39
00:02:05,920 --> 00:02:06,880
through the nose

40
00:02:07,380 --> 00:02:08,080
gently

41
00:02:08,320 --> 00:02:10,120
not flaring the nostrils

42
00:02:10,840 --> 00:02:12,000
easy in

43
00:02:13,300 --> 00:02:14,780
and easy out

44
00:02:16,360 --> 00:02:17,620
a nice smooth

45
00:02:18,000 --> 00:02:18,980
and even

46
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:21,440
rhythm of breathing

47
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,660
Once you feel that your body has slowed down a bit

48
00:02:28,280 --> 00:02:31,480
you might allow your body posture and facial expression

49
00:02:31,860 --> 00:02:33,300
to become compassionate

50
00:02:34,880 --> 00:02:38,920
Feel free to play around with postures and facial expressions

51
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:42,880
but whatever expression and posture you go with

52
00:02:43,540 --> 00:02:45,180
they should be gentle

53
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,920
Once you are ready

54
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:57,440
think of a time when someone was kind to you

55
00:02:59,080 --> 00:03:01,420
Not a time when you were in distress

56
00:03:02,420 --> 00:03:04,760
just a time when someone was kind to you

57
00:03:05,580 --> 00:03:08,380
A time when someone treated you with compassion

58
00:03:09,040 --> 00:03:09,840
grace

59
00:03:10,780 --> 00:03:11,580
dignity

60
00:03:12,600 --> 00:03:13,940
or kindness

61
00:03:32,580 --> 00:03:35,280
Put on your compassionate expression

62
00:03:35,640 --> 00:03:38,320
and adopt the compassionate body posture

63
00:03:38,660 --> 00:03:40,120
you have cultivated

64
00:03:40,380 --> 00:03:42,960
as you remember the compassion you received

65
00:03:44,800 --> 00:03:47,600
Recall how it felt to receive that kindness

66
00:03:57,020 --> 00:03:58,520
Spend a minute thinking

67
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,540
about the expressions of the person who was kind to you

68
00:04:01,700 --> 00:04:02,840
and mimicking them

69
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:04,480
if that helps

70
00:04:05,940 --> 00:04:08,020
