00:04:09,280 --> 00:04:11,400
imagine the person moving towards you

72
00:04:11,800 --> 00:04:13,600
with a smile on their face

73
00:04:13,740 --> 00:04:15,820
or their head tilted to one side

74
00:04:28,480 --> 00:04:30,360
While recalling the memory

75
00:04:30,940 --> 00:04:33,420
focus on the important sensory qualities

76
00:04:33,700 --> 00:04:34,860
of your memory

77
00:04:36,680 --> 00:04:38,620
Try the following steps

78
00:04:41,480 --> 00:04:42,280
One

79
00:04:43,740 --> 00:04:46,240
Focus on the kinds of things this person
said

80
00:04:46,360 --> 00:04:49,360
as well as the tone of their voice when the spoke

81
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,580
Spend a minute thinking

82
00:04:53,780 --> 00:04:56,200
about the kind things that this person said

83
00:05:17,060 --> 00:05:17,780
Next

84
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:22,360
focus on the feeling of the emotion in the person

85
00:05:23,120 --> 00:05:26,080
what they really felt for you at the moment

86
00:05:26,980 --> 00:05:29,340
Focus on that for another minute

87
00:05:51,960 --> 00:05:52,720
Finally

88
00:05:53,660 --> 00:05:56,220
focus on the entire experience

89
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:01,260
Think about whether they touched you in a friendly or comforting way

90
00:06:02,600 --> 00:06:05,160
or whether they helped you in some other way

91
00:06:07,160 --> 00:06:09,480
Allow the experience of gratitude

92
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:13,260
and joy in being helped grow
inside of you

93
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:18,920
Remember to keep your expression as compassionate as you can

94
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,600
Spend a few minutes in this step

95
00:07:04,740 --> 00:07:06,060
When you are ready

96
00:07:07,280 --> 00:07:10,180
let the memory gently fade away

97
00:07:12,160 --> 00:07:14,680
Come slowly out of the exercise

98
00:07:15,740 --> 00:07:17,780
and allow this feeling of compassion

99
00:07:19,260 --> 00:07:20,420
and kindness

100
00:07:20,980 --> 00:07:23,100
to carry into the rest of your day

101
00:07:23,900 --> 00:07:25,900
and your interactions with others

102
